daniel greene transformative learning technologies laboratory home about publications projects people teaching media fablearn 2011 home people daniel greene daniel greene position phd students daniel greene is a doctoral student in the learning sciences & technology design program at the stanford university school of education he applies cognitive science to the design and assessment of hands on learning environments for science and mathematics he is currently investigating the pedagogical applications of rapid fabrication tools daniel lives in palo alto and enjoys teaching learning and spending time in nature people faculty visiting researchers phd students ma students ms students undergraduate students high school interns collaborators alumni transformative learning technologies lab school of education stanford university 520 galvez mall room 102 ceras building stanford california 94305 usa connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr copyright 2011 all rights reserved top
